caption: We met with friends at this place for a meeting. my friend recommended this restaurant.  Well, we were not disappointed. we were warmly welcomed by the staff members  and we had a fantastic feeling. The meal was great. We had a great time and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Highly recommended.
Excellent! Mouth melting omakase! Thank you Hiro Kobayashi-San! One of the best sushi spots in the whole NYC. If you know what is the right sushi is - you definitely will understand.
The place offers a nice range of delicious food. I like eating here. The employees are always super nice, pricing is reasonable and the spot is always well organised.
Great omakase and service
What a gem in crown heights, very very good sushi!

We had omakase dinner for two. REALLY good quality food for really good price. $65 for salad, 10 pieces of sushi (toro, king salmon, kampachi, red snapper, saba, uni, etc), a toro maki roll, and miso soup. We had kumamoto oysters and fish liver for appetizers. Salmon, uni, and toro were delicious so we got a few more of those! I'm so glad we dined here! See you again :)

I have eaten omakase at the bar over the last couple years but am just now reviewing their takeout. The fish and service has always been outstanding (otherworldly for Brooklyn sushi standards) - so I immediately worried such a special place would crumble during COVID. It’s a joy that, not only are Uotora transforming and thriving, but also the delivery has surpassed any I’ve tried since the city shut down. This included driving to most of our favorite Manhattan spots for pickup that didn’t Caviar outside the borough. Definitely a different experience yet equally tasty and unique feeling, which is hard to achieve. Uotora chef maintains the intimate, lux night out feel instead of converting to your average roll spot. Congrats to them!
This place is superb and broad, the meals was delicious and the rates were very inexpensive. fast, efficient service and very personal staff members. I highly recommend this place.

Maybe their in-store food quality is way better. But I ordered delivery and it was horrible. The quality nor the quantity of the sushi justify its price. I'm a frequent sushi eater and this place is clearly selling bad fish at top price. AVOID!!!

From the moment  you come to that restaurant  the waiters give you a pleasant feeling. Very congenial stuff, it is a good place to  enjoy with buddies or with your date. heavenly  food, talented  chief cook and stuff, competitive  pay and courteous  service. Warmly recommended.

So overpriced. This is a bad picture but each of these “seaweed salads” was 8 dollars! We were shocked to the point of laughing when we received our order because it was so, so small, and we paid $170. we thought it was a mistake, so we called immediately and the woman we spoke to told me their appetizers are “bite-sized”... as is everything else apparently. Anyway, we feel bad writing this cause the food is high quality and I don’t want to hurt any business, but the value is so low because everything is sooo small and overpriced. And we’re not huge portion family either. I’m sorry guys, but you’re ripping people off and you know it :(.

An unassuming cozy place to get some high quality nigiri. Mackerel, uni, sweet shrimp and golden eye snapper are some of my favorites. You don’t want to end the omakase experiences without the hojicha ice cream sandwich and the strawberry daifuku. The ice cream sandwich has crispy shells with roasted earthy creamy filling (mixed with my loved red beans;) The skin of daifuku is soft and snowy, melting in my mouth. If anything could be better, I wish to sit by the counter and enjoy the omakase. Also, why I didn’t get tamago????
This spot clearly knows how to please their customers. Regularly with a nice attitude. The food is affordably priced, constantly fresh and clean.

The quality of fish is wonderful. The sushi rice is perfect. It’s clear the chefs care a great deal about the food they make. I’ve been frequenting this restaurant since they opened and the quality hasn’t diminished even as they had to switch from dine-in to take out. I highly recommend this place for anyone who is a fan of of high quality sushi.
First time order for delivery and i am very dissappointed. Came with completely destroyed box and sushi’s are separated between rice and sashimi. They don’t answer the phone.
Excellent

The service was great. Very knowledgeable and attentive staff. It was nicely and simply decorated. Beautiful without being distracting. Every fish was fresh or cured very cleanly. But I found the shari to be a bit too small overall and lacked mouthfeel. It helped focus on the textures of the fish but almost did not feel or taste the rice.
We’re lucky to have this spot in crown heights!
This incredible gem has the freshest sushi I've had outside of Toklyo. It is better than Masa Bar was 10 years ago.
LOVELY dinner! Went for my BF's birthday and did the sushi/sashimi Omakase, it was delicious and i highly recommend. The staff was friendly and attentive. Would definitely go back

Supposedly this place opened about a year ago. I didn't know until two months ago. An authentic sushi restaurant in walking distance. And their Omakase (you trust me) course is around $70, which can be over $100 in Manhattan. When I went there they still didn't have liquor licence so I had non alcohol Heineken which was fine keeping my drinking bill to the minimum. I wanted to try their sushi. I sat at the counter. Two sushi chefs there formally worked at Sushi Gari, so they are real pro. Each nigiri is freshly made right in front of you with some explanation about.each fish. My gave me about 11 pieces of nigiri on Omakase. They were really great. I had order four more white fish. Each different and unheard of. They were fantastic. I will definitely go back there. Maybe on my birthday.

Omakase is a great value, quality fish with interesting preparations - especially loved the NZ King Salmon and scallop. Fun chef to talk with as well, recommend sitting at the bar to chat

Uotora deserves 100 stars. The omakase is delicious. What really sets them apart is their service. The attentiveness to the customer’s needs and rhythm was truly Japanese. Everyone greets in Japanese, even though most of staff aren’t Japanese, and that sincerity packaged in the extreme amount of hospitality. Even the way the space was designed (the readiness of coatrack upon entry) was thoughtful.
Delicious sushi, great service, and a very relaxed and welcoming atmosphere. The omakase was perfect. Well worth a visit.
Some of the best sushi I’ve ever had. This place is lovely.
I’ve never been to Japan but my fiancé just got back and he loved this place, and I did too!  It’s simple but very good and authentic.
This place is amazing ! My husband and I love sushi and this is by far the best place we have ever been to. They are extremely nice and the sashimi is fresh and delicious. Going back next week !

Well done Chef ! I spend 1h45 there trying omakase, nice selection of fishs. I discover some new fish there. The team are really kind and friendly. The best in this area with Katsuei Sushis. But I prefer the room/bar and the service if I can compare ! Chef Denis from france ✌

I came here after hearing a new Omakase spot opened in crown heights. I came here on a Tuesday night and was happily seated at the bar for Omakase. As usual I get the Japanese greetings and sat down. There's an Ala cart menu but that doesn't get you a seat at the bar. I think Omakase let's you sit at the bar top. The place decor is minimal and cozy. Omakase is chefs choice 10 piece plus a Toro handroll and soup for 70 dollars. Before you finish the chef would offer any extra pieces please try the needle fish as it is in season as of now December! The sweet shrimp is definitely a must try. As you are served you get to see him orchestrate your food as he explains whats being plated in front of you. After the meal I chatted it up with my chef and was just very happy with them in general. I'm very glad Alot of Japanese chefs have decided to set up shop in New York city. My meal was about 120 dollars after tip and will happily come here again with my girlfriend. Give em a shot I'm sue you'll be satisfied with the Omakase experience they provide. Japanese food is an art and I think everyone should try it out!
Delicious one of the best Japanese experience in the city!!
This place is amazing. A shining example.of minimalism with purpose. No frills. Everything chosen impeccably. I happened to have e a sweet tooth at the time, the ice cream sandwich was to die for.

A true hidden gem in Crown Heights. The omakase is ridiculously cheap but impeccable quality!

This is some of the best food I have ever put in my mouth.  You're getting served by one of the owners and founders, guaranteed.  If you're looking for the authentic "Jiro Dreams of Sushi" experience in New York, this is where it's going to be had the most inexpensively.  The fish is imported from Japan daily, not overchilled, and prepared in the most authentic and caring way possible.  Each piece is made just for you (if you order Omakase at the counter).  I had types of fish I'd never heard of and I closed my eyes every time.  The rice is slightly pink, since it's made with authentic red sushi vinegar instead of the cheaper white kind.  The wasabi is then genuine spicier kind, not horseradish with green dye. This kind of place is what makes life worth living for me.
Restaurant is great. Chef remembers me by name. Chef even remembers I eat with my left hand and positions the sushi that makes it more convenient to grab by hand. Sushi is also amazing.
Delicious! Sit at the bar to enjoy the chef's selection and company. Everything is fresh and beautifully prepared. A great address!
Fantastically fresh and authentic Japanese food served by the owners who love what they do and you feel it. I'll certainly be back regularly.
Sushi deluxe, basic but well above average. Haven't tried omikase yet. Soft shell crab app A+. No alcohol as of 714/18.
This place is amazing and the staff is super friendly, possibly the best sushi in Brooklyn

5.27.18 - Surprisingly really good. The fish is very fresh and it includes a variety from Spain. I prefer the rice to be warmer, but it's seasoned well. The service is spot on and the interior is a simple design.  So the fish is sourced from Spain, Hokkaido, and the US West Coast. We went for the Omakase, which started with 3 bite size appetizers followed by 12 sushi pieces, and then finishing off with a handroll and the tamagoyaki.  Tonight's highlights include fresh octopus from Hokkaido (not sure how fresh can fresh get) and Spanish Yellowtail Tuna. The Spanish Yellowtail Tuna was super creamy; it was very surprising as I've never had tuna that was creamy.  I recommend reservations, but you can still get a table as a walk-in, but it's not very likely.
Simple but top quality Japanese food without a hefty price tag. Some of the best food in the neighborhood. Playing Fela Kuti around the clock doesn’t hurt either.

Uotora has very good food, and good service. However, the portion sizes are abysmal, and there are better omakase restaurants in Brooklyn at a similar price.  Uotora is a great restaurant for the Japanese dining experience, but a poor restaurant if you are looking for a good value. The cost they charge is not worth the dining experience you get.
